channel.title: Late Easter Challenge
channel.description:
I was planning to release this during Easter but, unfortunately, I didn't manage to finish it on time. So this Easter challenge has just become a late Easter Challenge.
#Difficulty I have no idea as I haven't tried to solve it myself... it may bevery easy or very tricky so here is a poll for the community to classify it
[poll type=regular] * Piece of Cake * Doable * Insane [/poll]
#Hints
Hint 1: [spoiler]The title of the post is the first hint... Easter...[/spoiler] Hint 2: [spoiler]You will get it when you need it[/spoiler]
# Rules Post the secret message using the sploit tag in the comments to demonstrate you made it
Be free to write up how you did it
# The challenge Copy the text below in a text file and then do the usual thing:
cat text_file.txt | base64 -d | gunzip > eo chmod 777 eo
_Note: As it looks like this challenge is a bit tricky than originally envisioned, this is a non striped version of the challenge that should be easier to solve... the binary is still obfuscated tho. As it looks like this challenge is a bit tricky than originally envisioned

Hey, I only just noticed this thread a couple of hours ago.

Jokes aside, @pry0cc, RE goes much deeper than just what is given to you in the clear. Understanding the macro (execution flow of the entire binary) and micro (code constructs which have specific patterns and behaviours) is a necessary skillset you need to develop. It will come in time but you have to start looking deeper and reading between the lines to evolve your mindset which will lead you to generate assumptions and conclusions to guide you to the correct path. RE is an art form and you need to take the time and effort to nurture it.
